<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1107">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/322</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                                State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-13">December 13, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Lord Halifax<note n="58" xml:id="d1107fn58">British Ambassador.</note>
                            called to see me today. He said he had just had word that his Foreign
                            Office felt our statement on the Lebanon<note n="59" xml:id="d1107fn59">Statement issued to the press by the Department of State, November
                                26, <ref target="#pg_1049">p. 1049</ref>.</note> was excellent and
                            that it pleased the British immensely.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>